.TH "devm_platform_ioremap_resource_byname" 9 "devm_platform_ioremap_resource_byname" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_platform_ioremap_resource_byname \- call devm_ioremap_resource for a platform device, retrieve the resource by name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" devm_platform_ioremap_resource_byname
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device to use both for memory resource lookup as well as
resource management
.IP "name" 12
name of the resource
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the remapped memory or an \fBERR_PTR\fP encoded error code
on failure.
